  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Hosea,
        the son of Beeri, in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings
        of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> first spoke through Hosea, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Hosea, \u201CGo, take to yourself a wife
        of whoredom and have children of whoredom, for the land commits great whoredom
        by forsaking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he went and took Gomer, the daughter of Diblaim, and she conceived
        and bore him a son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CCall his name
        Jezreel, for in just a little while I will punish the house of Jehu for the
        blood of Jezreel, and I will put an end to the kingdom of the house of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And on that day I will break the bow of Israel in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "She conceived again and bore a daughter. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to him, \u201CCall her name No Mercy,[[COMMENT(0)]] for I will no more
        have mercy on the house of Israel, to forgive them at all. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew , which means '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But I will have mercy on the house of Judah, and I will save them
        by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. I will not save them by bow
        or by sword or by war or by horses or by horsemen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When she had weaned No Mercy, she conceived and bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CCall his name Not
        My People,[[COMMENT(0)]] for you are not my people, and I am not your God.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew , which means Hebrew   '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] Yet the number of the children of Israel shall be
        like the sand of the sea, which cannot be measured or numbered. And in the
        place where it was said to them, \u201CYou are not my people,\u201D it shall
        be said to them, \u201CChildren of the living God.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: '  Ch 2:1 in Hebrew  Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And the children of Judah and the children of Israel shall be gathered
        together, and they shall appoint for themselves one head. And they shall
        go up from the land, for great shall be the day of Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness Punished"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness Punished"
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]] Say to your brothers, \u201CYou are my people,\u201D
        and to your sisters, \u201CYou have received mercy.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Ch 2:3 in Hebrew  Hebrew , which means Hebrew , which means '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlead with your mother, plead\u2014for she is not my wife,and
        I am not her husband\u2014that she put away her whoring from her face,and
        her adultery from between her breasts;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'lest I strip her nakedand make her as in the day she was born,and
        make her like a wilderness,and make her like a parched land,and kill her
        with thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Upon her children also I will have no mercy,  because they are
        children of whoredom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For their mother has played the whore;she who conceived them has
        acted shamefully.For she said, \u2018I will go after my lovers,who give me
        my bread and my water,my wool and my flax, my oil and my drink.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore I will hedge up her[[COMMENT(0)]] way with thorns,and I
        will build a wall against her,so that she cannot find her paths.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "She shall pursue her loversbut not overtake them,and she shall seek
        thembut shall not find them.  Then she shall say,\u2018I will go and return
        to my first husband,  for it was better for me then than now.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And she did not knowthat it was I who gave her  the grain, the wine,
        and the oil,and who lavished on her silver and gold,  which they used for
        Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore I will take backmy grain in its time,and my wine in its
        season,and I will take away my wool and my flax,which were to cover her nakedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now I will uncover her lewdnessin the sight of her lovers,and no
        one shall rescue her out of my hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And I will put an end to all her mirth,her feasts, her new moons,
        her Sabbaths,and all her appointed feasts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And I will lay waste her vines and her fig trees,  of which she said,\u2018These
        are my wages,which my lovers have given me.\u2019I will make them a forest, 
        and the beasts of the field shall devour them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The \u2019s Mercy on Israel"
      title: "The \u2019s Mercy on Israel"
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will punish her for the feast days of the Baalswhen she burned
        offerings to themand adorned herself with her ring and jewelry,and went after
        her loversand forgot me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, I will allure her,and bring her into the
        wilderness,and speak tenderly to her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And there I will give her her vineyardsand make the Valley of Achor[[COMMENT(0)]]
        a door of hope.And there she shall answer as in the days of her youth,as
        at the time when she came out of the land of Egypt.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: means ; compare Joshua 7:26
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd in that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you will call me \u2018My Husband,\u2019 and no longer will you call me \u2018My
        Baal.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For I will remove the names of the Baals from her mouth, and they
        shall be remembered by name no more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And I will make for them a covenant on that day with the beasts of
        the field, the birds of the heavens, and the creeping things of the ground.
        And I will abolish[[COMMENT(0)]] the bow, the sword, and war from the land,
        and I will make you lie down in safety. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will betroth you to me forever. I will betroth you to me in
        righteousness and in justice, in steadfast love and in mercy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will betroth you to me in faithfulness. And you shall know the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd in that day I will answer, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,I
        will answer the heavens,and they shall answer the earth,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and the earth shall answer the grain, the wine, and the oil,and they
        shall answer Jezreel,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and I will sow her for myself in the land.And I will have mercy on
        No Mercy,[[COMMENT(0)]]and I will say to Not My People,  \u2018You are my
        people\u2019;and he shall say, \u2018You are my God.\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hosea Redeems His Wife'
      title: Hosea Redeems His Wife
      number: 1
      content: "  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CGo again,
        love a woman who is loved by another man and is an adulteress, even as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> loves the children of Israel, though they turn
        to other gods and love cakes of raisins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought her for fifteen shekels of silver and a homer and a lethech[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of barley. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams; a was about 6 bushels or 220
          liters; a was about 3 bushels or 110 liters
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to her, \u201CYou must dwell as mine for many days. You
        shall not play the whore, or belong to another man; so will I also be to
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the children of Israel shall dwell many days without king or
        prince, without sacrifice or pillar, without ephod or household gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Afterward the children of Israel shall return and seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God, and David their king, and they shall come in fear to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and to his goodness in the latter days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Accuses Israel'
      title: The  Accuses Israel
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        O children of Israel,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has a controversy
        with the inhabitants of the land.There is no faithfulness or steadfast love,and
        no knowledge of God in the land;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  there is swearing, lying, murder, stealing, and committing adultery;they
        break all bounds, and bloodshed follows bloodshed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore the land mourns,and all who dwell in it languish,  and
        also the beasts of the fieldand the birds of the heavens,  and even the fish
        of the sea are taken away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Yet let no one contend,and let none accuse,for with you is my contention,
        O priest.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall stumble by day;the prophet also shall stumble with you
        by night;and I will destroy your mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge;  because you have
        rejected knowledge,I reject you from being a priest to me.And since you have
        forgotten the law of your God,  I also will forget your children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The more they increased,the more they sinned against me;  I will
        change their glory into shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  They feed on the sin[[COMMENT(0)]] of my people;they are greedy
        for their iniquity.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  And it shall be like people, like priest;I will punish them for
        their waysand repay them for their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  They shall eat, but not be satisfied;they shall play the whore,
        but not multiply,because they have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>to
        cherish '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'whoredom, wine, and new wine,which take away the understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'My people inquire of a piece of wood,and their walking staff gives
        them oracles.For a spirit of whoredom has led them astray,and they have left
        their God to play the whore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  They sacrifice on the tops of the mountainsand burn offerings on
        the hills,  under oak, poplar, and terebinth,because their shade is good.Therefore
        your daughters play the whore,and your brides commit adultery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will not punish your daughters when they play the whore,nor your
        brides when they commit adultery;for the men themselves go aside with prostitutesand
        sacrifice with cult prostitutes,and a people without understanding shall
        come to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Though you play the whore, O Israel,let not Judah become guilty. 
        Enter not into Gilgal,nor go up to Beth-aven,and swear not, \u201CAs the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Like a stubborn heifer,Israel is stubborn;can the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        now feed themlike a lamb in a broad pasture?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Ephraim is joined to idols;  leave him alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When their drink is gone, they give themselves to whoring;  their
        rulers[[COMMENT(0)]] dearly love shame.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  A wind has wrapped them[[COMMENT(0)]] in its wings,and they shall
        be ashamed because of their sacrifices.'
      comments:
      - number: '4:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Punishment Coming for Israel and Judah'
      title: Punishment Coming for Israel and Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    Hear this, O priests!Pay attention, O house of Israel!Give ear,
        O house of the king!For the judgment is for you;for you have been a snare
        at Mizpahand a net spread upon Tabor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the revolters have gone deep into slaughter,but I will discipline
        all of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  I know Ephraim,and Israel is not hidden from me;for now, O Ephraim,
        you have played the whore;Israel is defiled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Their deeds do not permit themto return to their God.For the spirit
        of whoredom is within them,and they know not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The pride of Israel testifies to his face;[[COMMENT(0)]]Israel
        and Ephraim shall stumble in his guilt;  Judah also shall stumble with them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  With their flocks and herds they shall goto seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        but they will not find him;  he has withdrawn from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  They have dealt faithlessly with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;for
        they have borne alien children.Now the new moon shall devour them with their
        fields.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Blow the horn in Gibeah,the trumpet in Ramah.Sound the alarm at
        Beth-aven;we follow you,[[COMMENT(0)]] O Benjamin!  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ephraim shall become a desolationin the day of punishment;among the
        tribes of IsraelI make known what is sure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The princes of Judah have becomelike those who move the landmark;upon
        them I will pour outmy wrath like water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim is oppressed, crushed in judgment,because he was determined
        to go after filth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I am like a moth to Ephraim,and like dry rot to the house of
        Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Ephraim saw his sickness,and Judah his wound,then Ephraim went
        to Assyria,and sent to the great king.[[COMMENT(0)]]  But he is not able
        to cure youor heal your wound.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For I will be like a lion to Ephraim,and like a young lion to the
        house of Judah.  I, even I, will tear and go away;I will carry off, and no
        one shall rescue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  I will return again to my place,until they acknowledge their guilt
        and seek my face,and in their distress earnestly seek me.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel and Judah Are Unrepentant'
      title: Israel and Judah Are Unrepentant
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCome, let us return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;for
        he has torn us, that he may heal us;he has struck us down, and he will bind
        us up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'After two days he will revive us;on the third day he will raise us
        up,that we may live before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  Let us know; let us press on to know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        his going out is sure as the dawn;he will come to us as the showers,  as
        the spring rains that water the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What shall I do with you, O Ephraim?What shall I do with you, O Judah?Your
        love is like a morning cloud,  like the dew that goes early away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore I have hewn them by the prophets;I have slain them by the
        words of my mouth,and my judgment goes forth as the light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I desire steadfast love[[COMMENT(0)]] and not sacrifice,  the
        knowledge of God rather than burnt offerings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But like Adam they transgressed the covenant;  there they dealt faithlessly
        with me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Gilead is a city of evildoers,  tracked with blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'As robbers lie in wait for a man,so the priests band together;they
        murder on the way to Shechem;they commit villainy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In the house of Israel I have seen a horrible thing;  Ephraim\u2019s
        whoredom is there; Israel is defiled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For you also, O Judah, a harvest is appointed.When I restore the fortunes
        of my people,
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    when I would heal Israel,the iniquity of Ephraim is revealed,and
        the evil deeds of Samaria,for they deal falsely;the thief breaks in,and the
        bandits raid outside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But they do not considerthat I remember all their evil.Now their
        deeds surround them;  they are before my face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By their evil they make the king glad,and the princes by their treachery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  They are all adulterers;they are like a heated ovenwhose baker
        ceases to stir the fire,from the kneading of the doughuntil it is leavened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the day of our king, the princesbecame sick with the heat of wine;he
        stretched out his hand with mockers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For with hearts like an oven they approach their intrigue;all night
        their anger smolders;in the morning it blazes like a flaming fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All of them are hot as an oven,and they devour their rulers.All their
        kings have fallen,and none of them calls upon me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim mixes himself with the peoples;Ephraim is a cake not turned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Strangers devour his strength,and he knows it not;gray hairs are
        sprinkled upon him,and he knows it not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The pride of Israel testifies to his face;[[COMMENT(0)]]  yet they
        do not return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God,nor seek him,
        for all this.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim is like a dove,  silly and without sense,calling to Egypt,
        going to Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As they go, I will spread over them my net;I will bring them down
        like birds of the heavens;  I will discipline them according to the report
        made to their congregation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Woe to them, for they have strayed from me!Destruction to them,
        for they have rebelled against me!  I would redeem them,but they speak lies
        against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  They do not cry to me from the heart,but they wail upon their beds;for
        grain and wine they gash themselves;they rebel against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Although I trained and strengthened their arms,yet they devise evil
        against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They return, but not upward;[[COMMENT(0)]]they are like a treacherous
        bow;their princes shall fall by the swordbecause of the insolence of their
        tongue.This shall be their derision in the land of Egypt.
      comments:
      - number: '7:16 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Will Reap the Whirlwind'
      title: Israel Will Reap the Whirlwind
      number: 1
      content: '  Set the trumpet to your lips!One like a vulture is over the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,because they have transgressed my covenantand
        rebelled against my law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "To me they cry,  \u201CMy God, we\u2014Israel\u2014know you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Israel has spurned the good;the enemy shall pursue him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  They made kings, but not through me.They set up princes, but I
        knew it not.With their silver and gold they made idolsfor their own destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  I have[[COMMENT(0)]] spurned your calf, O Samaria.My anger burns
        against them.  How long will they be incapable of innocence?  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For it is from Israel;a craftsman made it;it is not God.  The calf
        of Samaria  shall be broken to pieces.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For they sow the wind,and they shall reap the whirlwind.The standing
        grain has no heads;it shall yield no flour;if it were to yield,  strangers
        would devour it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Israel is swallowed up;already they are among the nationsas a useless
        vessel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For they have gone up to Assyria,  a wild donkey wandering alone;Ephraim
        has hired lovers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Though they hire allies among the nations,I will soon gather them
        up.And the king and princes shall soon writhebecause of the tribute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because Ephraim has multiplied altars for sinning,they have become
        to him altars for sinning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Were I to write for him my laws by the ten thousands,they would
        be regarded as a strange thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As for my sacrificial offerings,  they sacrifice meat and eat it,but
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not accept them.  Now he will remember
        their iniquityand punish their sins;  they shall return to Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For Israel has forgotten his Makerand built palaces,and Judah has
        multiplied fortified cities;so I will send a fire upon his cities,and it
        shall devour her strongholds.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Will Punish Israel'
      title: The  Will Punish Israel
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Rejoice not, O Israel!Exult not like
        the peoples;  for you have played the whore, forsaking your God.  You have
        loved a prostitute\u2019s wageson all threshing floors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Threshing floor and wine vat shall not feed them,and the new wine
        shall fail them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They shall not remain in the land of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        Ephraim shall return to Egypt,and they shall eat unclean food in Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  They shall not pour drink offerings of wine to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        and their sacrifices shall not please him.It shall be like mourners\u2019
        bread to them;all who eat of it shall be defiled;for their bread shall be
        for their hunger only;  it shall not come to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  What will you do on the day of the appointed festival,and on the
        day of the feast of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For behold, they are going away from destruction;but Egypt shall
        gather them;Memphis shall bury them.Nettles shall possess their precious
        things of silver;  thorns shall be in their tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The days of punishment have come;the days of recompense have come;Israel
        shall know it.  The prophet is a fool;the man of the spirit is mad,because
        of your great iniquityand great hatred.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The prophet is the watchman of Ephraim with my God;yet a fowler\u2019s
        snare is on all his ways,and hatred in the house of his God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  They have deeply corrupted themselvesas in the days of Gibeah: 
        he will remember their iniquity;he will punish their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Like grapes in the wilderness,  I found Israel.Like the first fruit
        on the fig treein its first season,I saw your fathers.But they came to Baal-peorand
        consecrated themselves to the thing of shame,and became detestable like the
        thing they loved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ephraim\u2019s glory shall fly away like a bird\u2014  no birth,
        no pregnancy, no conception!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Even if they bring up children,I will bereave them till none is
        left.  Woe to themwhen I depart from them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ephraim, as I have seen, was like a young palm[[COMMENT(0)]] planted
        in a meadow;but Ephraim must lead his children out to slaughter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Give them, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014what will you give?Give
        them a miscarrying womband dry breasts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Every evil of theirs is in Gilgal;there I began to hate them.Because
        of the wickedness of their deedsI will drive them out of my house.I will
        love them no more;all their princes are rebels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ephraim is stricken;  their root is dried up;they shall bear no fruit.Even
        though they give birth,  I will put their beloved children to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  My God will reject thembecause they have not listened to him; 
        they shall be wanderers among the nations.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Israel is a luxuriant vinethat yields its fruit.The more his
        fruit increased,  the more altars he built;as his country improved,he improved
        his pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their heart is false;now they must bear their guilt.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will break down their altarsand destroy their pillars.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For now they will say:  \u201CWe have no king,for we do not fear
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;and a king\u2014what could he do for us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They utter mere words;with empty[[COMMENT(0)]] oaths they make covenants;so
        judgment springs up like poisonous weeds  in the furrows of the field.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: Or (see Exodus 20:7)
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The inhabitants of Samaria tremblefor the calf[[COMMENT(0)]] of Beth-aven.Its
        people mourn for it, and so do its idolatrous priests\u2014those who rejoiced
        over it and over its glory\u2014for it has departed from them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The thing itself shall be carried to Assyriaas tribute to the great
        king.[[COMMENT(0)]]Ephraim shall be put to shame,and Israel shall be ashamed
        of his idol.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  Samaria\u2019s king shall perishlike a twig on the face of the
        waters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The high places of Aven, the sin of Israel,shall be destroyed.  Thorn
        and thistle shall grow upon their altars,and they shall say to the mountains,
        \u201CCover us,\u201Dand to the hills, \u201CFall on us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'From the days of Gibeah, you have sinned, O Israel;there they have
        continued.Shall not the war against the unjust[[COMMENT(0)]] overtake them
        in Gibeah?  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  When I please, I will discipline them,and nations shall be gathered
        against themwhen they are bound up for their double iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim was a trained calfthat loved to thresh,and I spared her fair
        neck;but I will put Ephraim to the yoke;  Judah must plow;Jacob must harrow
        for himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Sow for yourselves righteousness;reap steadfast love;  break up
        your fallow ground,for it is the time to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,that
        he may come and rain righteousness upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  You have plowed iniquity;you have reaped injustice;you have eaten
        the fruit of lies.Because you have trusted in your own wayand in the multitude
        of your warriors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'therefore the tumult of war shall arise among your people,and all
        your fortresses shall be destroyed,as Shalman destroyed Beth-arbel on the
        day of battle;  mothers were dashed in pieces with their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Thus it shall be done to you, O Bethel,because of your great evil.At
        dawn the king of Israelshall be utterly cut off.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Love for Israel"
      title: "The \u2019s Love for Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    When Israel was a child, I loved him,and
        out of Egypt I called my son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The more they were called,the more they went away;  they kept sacrificing
        to the Baalsand burning offerings to idols.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yet it was I who taught Ephraim to walk;I took them up by their arms,but
        they did not know that I healed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  I led them with cords of kindness,[[COMMENT(0)]]with the bands
        of love,and I became to them as one who eases the yoke on their jaws,and
        I bent down to them and fed them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  They shall not[[COMMENT(0)]] return to the land of Egypt,but Assyria
        shall be their king,  because they have refused to return to me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The sword shall rage against their cities,consume the bars of their
        gates,and devour them because of their own counsels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My people are bent on turning away from me,and though they call out
        to the Most High,he shall not raise them up at all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'How can I give you up, O Ephraim?How can I hand you over, O Israel? 
        How can I make you like Admah?How can I treat you like Zeboiim?  My heart
        recoils within me;my compassion grows warm and tender.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will not execute my burning anger;I will not again destroy Ephraim; 
        for I am God and not a man,  the Holy One in your midst,and I will not come
        in wrath.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:9 '
        content: 'Or   '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  They shall go after the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  he will roar
        like a lion;when he roars,his children shall come trembling from the west;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'they shall come trembling like birds from Egypt,and like doves from
        the land of Assyria,and I will return them to their homes, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] Ephraim has surrounded me with lies,and the house
        of Israel with deceit,but Judah still walks with Godand is faithful to the
        Holy One.'
      comments:
      - number: '11:12 '
        content: '  Ch 12:1 in Hebrew  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Indictment of Israel and Judah"
      title: "The \u2019s Indictment of Israel and Judah"
      number: 1
      content: '  Ephraim feeds on the windand pursues the east wind all day long;they
        multiply falsehood and violence;  they make a covenant with Assyria,and oil
        is carried to Egypt.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has an indictment against Judahand
        will punish Jacob according to his ways;he will repay him according to his
        deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  In the womb he took his brother by the heel,and in his manhood
        he strove with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He strove with the angel and prevailed;he wept and sought his favor. 
        He met God[[COMMENT(0)]] at Bethel,and there God spoke with us\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts,  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is his memorial name:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CSo you, by the help of your God, return,  hold fast to love
        and justice,and wait continually for your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A merchant, in whose hands are false balances,he loves to oppress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ephraim has said, \u201CAh, but I am rich;I have found wealth for
        myself;in all my labors they cannot find in me iniquity or sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your Godfrom the land of Egypt;I
        will again make you dwell in tents,as in the days of the appointed feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  I spoke to the prophets;it was I who multiplied visions,and through
        the prophets gave parables.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  If there is iniquity in Gilead,they shall surely come to nothing: 
        in Gilgal they sacrifice bulls;  their altars also are like stone heaps 
        on the furrows of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Jacob fled to the land of Aram;there Israel served for a wife,and
        for a wife he guarded sheep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'By a prophet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought Israel up from
        Egypt,and by a prophet he was guarded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Ephraim has given bitter provocation;so his Lord will leave his
        bloodguilt on him  and will repay him for his disgraceful deeds.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Relentless Judgment on Israel"
      title: "The \u2019s Relentless Judgment on Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  When Ephraim spoke, there was trembling; 
        he was exalted in Israel,but he incurred guilt through Baal and died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And now they sin more and more,and make for themselves metal images,idols
        skillfully made of their silver,  all of them the work of craftsmen.It is
        said of them,\u201CThose who offer human sacrifice kiss calves!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore they shall be like the morning mistor like the dew that
        goes early away,  like the chaff that swirls from the threshing flooror like
        smoke from a window.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your Godfrom the land of
        Egypt;  you know no God but me,and besides me there is no savior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  It was I who knew you in the wilderness,in the land of drought;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  but when they had grazed,[[COMMENT(0)]] they became full,  they
        were filled, and their heart was lifted up;  therefore they forgot me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I am to them like a lion;  like a leopard I will lurk beside the
        way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will fall upon them like a bear robbed of her cubs;I will tear
        open their breast,and there I will devour them like a lion,  as a wild beast
        would rip them open.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He destroys[[COMMENT(0)]] you, O Israel,for you are against me, against
        your helper.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  Where now is your king, to save you in all your cities?Where are
        all your rulers\u2014those of whom you said,\u201CGive me a king and princes\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  I gave you a king in my anger,and I took him away in my wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The iniquity of Ephraim is bound up;his sin is kept in store.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The pangs of childbirth come for him,but he is an unwise son,for
        at the right time he does not present himself  at the opening of the womb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  I shall ransom them from the power of Sheol;  I shall redeem them
        from Death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  O Death, where are your plagues?  O Sheol, where
        is your sting?  Compassion is hidden from my eyes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:14 '
        content: 'Or   '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Though he may flourish among his brothers,  the east wind, the wind
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, shall come,rising from the wilderness, 
        and his fountain shall dry up;his spring shall be parched;it shall strip
        his treasuryof every precious thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] Samaria shall bear her guilt,because she has rebelled
        against her God;they shall fall by the sword;  their little ones shall be
        dashed in pieces,and their pregnant women ripped open.'
      comments:
      - number: '13:16 '
        content: '  Ch 14:1 in Hebrew  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Plea to Return to the '
      title: 'A Plea to Return to the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Return, O Israel, to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,for you have stumbled because of your iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Take with you wordsand return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;say
        to him,\u201CTake away all iniquity;accept what is good,and we will pay with
        bulls  the vows[[COMMENT(0)]] of our lips.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  Assyria shall not save us;  we will not ride on horses;and we will
        say no more, \u2018Our God,\u2019to the work of our hands.  In you the orphan
        finds mercy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will heal their apostasy;  I will love them freely,for my anger
        has turned from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  I will be like the dew to Israel;  he shall blossom like the lily;he
        shall take root like the trees of Lebanon;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'his shoots shall spread out;his beauty shall be like the olive,and
        his fragrance like Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They shall return and dwell beneath my[[COMMENT(0)]] shadow;they
        shall flourish like the grain;they shall blossom like the vine;their fame
        shall be like the wine of Lebanon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Ephraim, what have I to do with idols?It is I who answer and look
        after you.[[COMMENT(0)]]I am like an evergreen cypress;  from me comes your
        fruit.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
